# Git Branch Safety

## Rules
- Run `git status` before any branch switch.
- Do not use `git stash` as a default conflict-avoidance step.
- If existing local changes affect git operations, incorporate those changes into the current work instead of stashing.
- When incorporated changes are included, update the change definition and scope so it explicitly reflects all included work.
- Ensure commit messages, PR titles, and PR descriptions all describe the full incorporated scope, not only the originally planned change.
- Prefer `git switch` over legacy branch commands.
- Do not run branch commands that can overwrite local changes unless explicitly requested.
- If work-loss risk exists, stop and confirm the safe path with the user.
